title: Teen dead after shooting at house party
content:
SNELLVILLE, GA (CBS46) -
Police are searching for the suspect responsible for the shooting death of a teen at a house party in Snellville early Saturday morning. The incident happened around 12:30 a.m. at a party attended by 30 to 40 people at a home on the 2900 block of Aviator Circle.
The teen has been identified as 17-year-old Jahlah Branch.
A dispute between several people at the party led to multiple shots being fired. When officers arrived on the scene, they found Branch dead with a gunshot wound to the head.
The suspect and others fled the scene. A description of the suspect has not been released.
Crime Stoppers are offering up to $2,000 for information leading to an arrest and indictment in the case. If you have any information regarding this case, you're urged to contact Gwinnett County Police.
